<h1>Welcome to Heavy-lifting</h1>
<p><span>Heavy-lifting is framework focused on the design, detail and operation of conveyor systems. It has been designed to emulate the functionality of the open source design framework&nbsp;<a href="https://github.com/"><span>GitHub</span></a>.</span></p>
<p><span>Heavy-lifting design focus has been to emulate the requirements for the git management network developed by Linus Torvalds in 2005.</span></p>
<p><span>At this point there is no cryptographic element id structure, but likely this will be added in the future.</span></p>
<h2>Core Design Parameters</h2>
<p><span>The following principles of design have been followed for the creation of the framework.</span></p>
<h3>Strong support for non-linear development</h3>
<p><span>The frame work is designed to support rapid branching and merging, and includes specific tools for visualizing and navigating the non-linear development history of your design history. A core design assumption of the framework is that a change will be merged more often than it is written, as it is passed around to various reviewers. </span></p>
<h3>Distributed development</h3>
<p><span>To ensure that the framework maintains validity in the constant flux of software and hardware development, the core functionality of the management system is an open source project, allowing for application in different environments.</span></p>
<h3>Compatibility with existent systems and protocols</h3>
<p><span>The framework is based on JSON objects, these objects have clearly defined structures that allow for simple exporting, importing and compatibility. </span></p>
<h3>Efficient handling of large projects</h3>
<p><span>The framework is focused on scalability, as each items revision tracking is handled with user and organizational control, projects can be copied and controlled on an element by element basis.</span></p>
 


